(uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'event-lisbon-festas-santo-antonio'),
 uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'city-lisbon'),
 'Festas de Lisboa & Santo António', 'lisbon-festas-santo-antonio', 'festival',
 'Lisbon''s biggest street party transforms the city throughout June, culminating on the night of June 12-13 with the Santo António festival. Neighborhoods compete in decorations, grilled sardines fill the air, and all-night street parties take over Alfama, Bairro Alto, and Graça with music, dancing, and traditional marchas parades.',
 'Stay in Baixa or Chiado for easy walk home from Alfama festivities - taxis are impossible after midnight. Keep valuables secure in crowded streets, bring cash for food stalls, and join locals early evening (8-10pm) before peak crowds.',
 6, 6, 'June 1-30, peak night June 12-13', 'annual',
 NULL, true, 'high', 1),

(uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'event-lisbon-pride'),
 uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'city-lisbon'),
 'Lisbon Pride (Arraial Pride)', 'lisbon-pride', 'parade',
 'One of Europe''s most welcoming Pride celebrations takes over Lisbon in mid-June with a week of parties, cultural events, and activism. The main parade marches from Marquês de Pombal to Terreiro do Paço, followed by a massive street party in Príncipe Real with stages, DJs, and food vendors.',
 'Príncipe Real is the safest, most women-friendly zone with well-lit streets and visible security. Book accommodation nearby or in Bairro Alto for easy access, and use official Pride app for event times and meeting points.',
 6, 6, 'Mid-June (dates vary)', 'annual',
 NULL, true, 'high', 2),

(uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'event-lisbon-rock-in-rio'),
 uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'city-lisbon'),
 'Rock in Rio Lisboa', 'lisbon-rock-in-rio', 'festival',
 'The legendary Brazilian music festival lands in Lisbon every other year (even years) at Parque da Bela Vista, bringing world-class rock, pop, and electronic acts across four days. Expect 80,000+ daily attendees, multiple stages, and performances from 2pm to 2am.',
 'Buy multi-day passes early for best prices, and book hotels near Oriente or Alameda metro stations for direct access to venue. Festival grounds are safe and well-policed, but travel in groups after dark and use official shuttle buses instead of unlicensed taxis.',
 6, 6, 'Late June (even years only: 2026, 2028)', 'annual',
 NULL, false, 'high', 3),

(uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'event-lisbon-sardine-festival'),
 uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'city-lisbon'),
 'Festival do Sardinha', 'lisbon-sardine-festival', 'festival',
 'This traditional food festival in early June celebrates Portugal''s sardine season with hundreds of grills set up along the riverfront in Terreiro do Paço and Cais do Sodré. Fresh sardines are served on bread with peppers and wine, accompanied by live fado and folk music performances.',
 'Arrive before 7pm to avoid longest lines at popular grills, and bring wet wipes as sardines are messy finger food. The riverside is well-lit and family-friendly, but watch your bag in dense crowds near the main stages.',
 6, 6, 'Early June (first weekend)', 'annual',
 NULL, false, 'high', 4),

(uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'event-porto-sao-joao'),
 uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'city-porto'),
 'Festa de São João', 'porto-sao-joao', 'festival',
 'Porto''s most iconic festival on the night of June 23-24 fills the streets with locals hitting each other with plastic hammers and leek flowers, grilling sardines on every corner, and launching lanterns into the sky. The party centers on Ribeira and Avenida dos Aliados, ending at sunrise on Praia dos Ingleses beach.',
 'Stay in Ribeira or Baixa for walking distance to festivities - bridges and streets become impassable after 11pm. Bring a plastic hammer from street vendors (€2), wear closed shoes for crowded cobblestones, and join the beach sunrise tradition with groups, not alone.',
 6, 6, 'Night of June 23-24', 'annual',
 NULL, true, 'high', 1),

(uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'event-porto-wine-harvest'),
 uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'city-porto'),
 'Porto Wine Harvest Festival', 'porto-wine-harvest', 'festival',
 'Celebrate the Douro Valley grape harvest in September with wine tastings, traditional foot-treading demonstrations, live music, and vineyard tours across Porto and Vila Nova de Gaia. Port wine houses open special cellars, offer discounts, and host harvest dinners with regional cuisine.',
 'Book winery tours in Douro Valley through reputable companies like Douro Exclusive or Living Tours for safe, women-friendly group experiences. In Porto, stick to established wine cellars in Gaia (Graham''s, Taylor''s, Sandeman) with clear closing times for solo visits.',
 9, 9, 'Mid-September (two weeks)', 'annual',
 NULL, false, 'moderate', 2),

(uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'event-porto-primavera-sound'),
 uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'city-porto'),
 'NOS Primavera Sound', 'porto-primavera-sound', 'festival',
 'This world-renowned indie and alternative music festival takes over Parque da Cidade in early June, featuring 200+ artists across four days on multiple stages. Known for its diverse lineup spanning rock, electronic, hip-hop, and experimental genres, it attracts 50,000+ international attendees.',
 'Festival grounds are safe with visible security and dedicated women''s rest areas, but book accommodation in Foz or Boavista neighborhoods for 20-minute walk home. Download the festival app for stage times and use the buddy system after midnight when crowds peak.',
 6, 6, 'Early June (four days)', 'annual',
 NULL, false, 'high', 3),

(uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'event-marrakech-film-festival'),
 uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'city-marrakech'),
 'Marrakech International Film Festival', 'marrakech-film-festival', 'festival',
 'Morocco''s premier film festival brings international cinema, A-list celebrities, and industry professionals to Marrakech every November or December. Screenings take place at Palais des Congrès and Jemaa el-Fna open-air cinema, with red carpet events, master classes, and industry panels.',
 'Book hotels in Hivernage or Guéliz for safer evening walks back from screenings, and dress conservatively even at glamorous events (covered shoulders, knee-length minimum). Use official festival transport or trusted grand taxis, never unmarked cabs after dark.',
 11, 12, 'Late November or early December (dates vary)', 'annual',
 NULL, false, 'moderate', 1),

(uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'event-marrakech-ramadan'),
 uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'city-marrakech'),
 'Ramadan in Marrakech', 'marrakech-ramadan', 'holiday',
 'Experience the spiritual heart of Morocco during the holy month of Ramadan, when the medina transforms at sunset with iftar meals, special prayers, and night markets. Jemaa el-Fna becomes a magical food festival after maghrib prayer, and riads offer traditional harira soup and dates to break the fast.',
 'Respect fasting hours by not eating/drinking/smoking in public during daylight, and dress more conservatively than usual (long sleeves, loose pants/skirts). Many restaurants are closed until sunset, so plan accordingly and book your riad''s iftar experience in advance for the best atmosphere.',
 3, 4, 'Dates shift yearly with Islamic calendar (approximately March-April)', 'annual',
 NULL, true, 'moderate', 2),

(uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'event-marrakech-popular-arts'),
 uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'city-marrakech'),
 'Marrakech Popular Arts Festival', 'marrakech-popular-arts', 'festival',
 'This vibrant celebration of Moroccan folk culture fills Jemaa el-Fna and El Badi Palace with traditional music, Berber dance troupes, snake charmers, acrobats, and storytellers for one week in July. Expect colorful processions, handicraft exhibitions, and nightly performances showcasing Morocco''s diverse regional traditions.',
 'Attend daytime performances at El Badi Palace for a more structured, tourist-friendly experience with seating and clear exits. For evening Jemaa el-Fna shows, stay near the main square''s well-lit café terraces and avoid isolated alleys when walking back to your riad.',
 7, 7, 'Early July (one week)', 'annual',
 NULL, true, 'high', 3),

(uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'event-fes-sacred-music'),
 uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'city-fes'),
 'Fes Festival of World Sacred Music', 'fes-sacred-music', 'festival',
 'One of the world''s most prestigious spiritual music festivals brings Sufi singers, gospel choirs, Buddhist monks, and sacred musicians from 40+ countries to Fes every June. Concerts take place in stunning venues like Bab Makina, Batha Museum gardens, and the Dar Tazi palace courtyard.',
 'Book tickets online in advance for popular evening concerts at Bab Makina, which sell out quickly. Stay in Ville Nouvelle for easier night navigation, and arrange riad pickup for medina venues - sacred music events are respectful and safe, but medina streets are confusing after dark.',
 6, 6, 'Mid-June (10 days)', 'annual',
 NULL, false, 'moderate', 1),

(uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'event-fes-ramadan'),
 uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'city-fes'),
 'Ramadan in Fes', 'fes-ramadan', 'holiday',
 'Fes, Morocco''s spiritual capital, offers the most authentic Ramadan experience with centuries-old mosques, pre-dawn suhoor drumming through medina alleys, and elaborate iftar spreads. The medieval medina becomes especially atmospheric at night with lantern-lit streets and the call to prayer echoing from Qarawiyyin Mosque.',
 'Most medina restaurants and cafés close entirely during Ramadan, so book a riad with meal service or stay in Ville Nouvelle where some tourist restaurants remain open. Hire a licensed female guide for daytime medina exploration, as fewer people are out and some areas feel isolated.',
 3, 4, 'Dates shift yearly with Islamic calendar (approximately March-April)', 'annual',
 NULL, true, 'low', 2),

(uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'event-fes-cherry-festival'),
 uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'city-fes'),
 'Fes Cherry Festival (Sefrou)', 'fes-cherry-festival', 'festival',
 'Just 30km from Fes, the charming mountain town of Sefrou hosts Morocco''s oldest festival celebrating the cherry harvest in June. Three days of parades, music, folk dancing, and cherry-themed everything, including the crowning of the Cherry Queen and traditional Amazigh performances.',
 'Join a day trip organized by your Fes riad or book a seat on the CTM bus to Sefrou (30 dirhams, 45 minutes). The festival is family-friendly and safe for solo travelers, but arrange return transport before 8pm as evening buses fill quickly.',
 6, 6, 'Mid-June (three days)', 'annual',
 NULL, true, 'moderate', 3),

(uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'event-chefchaouen-ramadan'),
 uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'city-chefchaouen'),
 'Ramadan in the Blue City', 'chefchaouen-ramadan', 'holiday',
 'Experience Ramadan in Morocco''s most serene setting, where the blue-washed medina takes on a magical quality at sunset when locals break their fast together. The intimate scale of Chefchaouen means you''ll be invited to share iftar with shopkeepers and neighbors, offering genuine cultural connection.',
 'Most medina restaurants close during fasting hours, so book accommodation with meal service or shop at small groceries near Uta el-Hammam square. The town is exceptionally safe for solo women during Ramadan, but dress conservatively and avoid hiking Rif trails alone during midday heat when few people are out.',
 3, 4, 'Dates shift yearly with Islamic calendar (approximately March-April)', 'annual',
 NULL, true, 'low', 1),

(uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'event-chefchaouen-alegria'),
 uuid_generate_v5(uuid_ns_url(), 'city-chefchaouen'),
 'Alegria Festival', 'chefchaouen-alegria', 'festival',
 'This emerging arts and music festival in late June or early July showcases Moroccan and international musicians, visual artists, and performers against the backdrop of Chefchaouen''s blue streets. Intimate concerts happen in riads, on rooftop terraces, and at Ras El Ma waterfall, celebrating creative fusion and cultural exchange.',
 'The festival attracts a bohemian, respectful crowd and is one of Morocco''s safest events for solo women travelers. Book your riad early as the town is small (only 200+ beds), and join the organized hikes to mountain venues rather than going alone.',
 6, 7, 'Late June or early July (dates vary)', 'annual',
 NULL, false, 'low', 2);
